description:
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for an Assistant Application Analyst to join our Application Support team. This team supports the Trust&#39;s key clinical information systems: SystmOne (TPP) and PiMS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be one of a team of five people supporting services and users of the above systems, and performing system management tasks including addressing data quality issues, configuration, troubleshooting and testing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must have experience of using SystmOne and preferably of supporting colleagues who use it. You will need to work closely and build relationships with a wide range of professionals including clinicians, clinical support staff, senior managers, suppliers and informatics colleagues. You must also have good verbal and written communication skills and a robust understanding of the healthcare environment and its processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be formally based in Brighton, and may be expected to travel to any of our 80 sites across Sussex. There is scope for the post to include working from home arrangements throughout the current pandemic - this will be discussed as per the individual needs of the applicant within the scope of the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is fixed term until 31 March 2022.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameMark ThreakallJob titleApplication Support ManagerEmail addressmark.threakall@nhs.netTelephone number07342 063998&lt;/p&gt;
